1) Encode your plain-text corpus data to a compressed binary form:
 
classencode -f yourcorpus

This results in a class file (yourcorpus.cls) and the encoded corpus (yourcorpus.clsenc)
 

2) Invoke the pattern finder on these files:

 patternfinder -f yourcorpus.clsenc
 
(See patternfinder -h for important options, including pruning thresholds)

This results in an ngram/skipgram model yourcorpus.clsenc.bin (binary) 
 
3) Decode the binary file back to a text file

 modeldecode -f yourcorpus.clsenc.bin -c yourcorpus.cls
